-- JPMorgan Names Energy Banker Castaldo Managing Director
-- B y   M a t t h e w   M o n k s
-- 2013-10-29T19:15:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-29/jpmorgan-names-energy-banker-castaldo-managing-director-1-.html
JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  has hired
Andrew Castaldo from  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  to help advise on oil
and gas deals, according to a memo obtained by Bloomberg News.  Castaldo will be based in New York report to Hernan Cristerna and Christopher Ventresca, JPMorgan’s global co-heads
of mergers and acquisitions, the document shows. The contents of
the memo were confirmed by the bank’s New York-based spokeswoman
 Tasha Pelio .  Castaldo, who worked at Citigroup Inc. before joining Bank
of America in 2006, helped advise Apache Corp. on its $7 billion
purchase of assets from BP Plc in 2010. He also worked on
Regency Energy Partners LP’s $5.6 billion acquisition of PVR
Partners LP, a natural gas pipeline and processing company,
which was announced this month.  Ventresca and Cristerna were named co-heads of global
mergers and in May amid an overhaul of the top management of the
team. Ventresca previously was JPMorgan’s head of North
American M&A, while Cristerna oversaw M&A for Europe,
Middle East and Africa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
